Package parser

The classes for the parser and the main compiler itself.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    JDCParserConstants
    Token literal values and constants.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    JavaCharStream
    An implementation of interface CharStream, where the stream is assumed to contain only ASCII characters (with java-like unicode escape processing).
    JavaDecafCompiler
    The main compiler class.
    JDCParser  
    JDCParserTokenManager
    Token Manager.
    StyleWarnings
    Class containing static method for generating style warnings.
    Token
    Describes the input token stream.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    ClassNameParseException
    Exception thrown when classname is not acceptable according to Java convention.
    CompilerException
    Exception thrown in the event of a problem finding the system compiler.
    MethodNameParseException
    Exception thrown when method name is not acceptable according to Java convention.
    ParseException
    This exception is thrown when parse errors are encountered.
    VariableNameParseException
    Exception thrown when variable name is not acceptable according to Java convention.
  • Error Summary 
    Error Description
    TokenMgrError
    Token Manager Error.
